7551 /******************************************************************************/
7552 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F3xx device product */
7553 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
7554 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
7555 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
7556 /* product lines within the same STM32F3 Family */
7557 /******************************************************************************/
7558 
7559 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
7560 
7561 #define ADC1_IRQn ADC1_2_IRQn
7562 #define USB_HP_CAN_TX_IRQn CAN_TX_IRQn
7563 #define USB_LP_CAN_RX0_IRQn CAN_RX0_IRQn
7564 #define TIM15_IRQn TIM1_BRK_TIM15_IRQn
7565 #define TIM16_IRQn TIM1_UP_TIM16_IRQn
7566 #define TIM17_IRQn TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM17_IRQn
7567 #define COMP_IRQn COMP2_IRQn
7568 #define COMP1_2_3_IRQn COMP2_IRQn
7569 #define COMP1_2_IRQn COMP2_IRQn
7570 #define COMP4_5_6_IRQn COMP4_6_IRQn
7571 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQn TIM6_DAC1_IRQn
7572 
7573 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
7574 #define ADC1_IRQHandler ADC1_2_IRQHandler
7575 #define USB_HP_CAN_TX_IRQHandler CAN_TX_IRQHandler
7576 #define USB_LP_CAN_RX0_IRQHandler CAN_RX0_IRQHandler
7577 #define TIM15_IRQHandler TIM1_BRK_TIM15_IRQHandler
7578 #define TIM16_IRQHandler TIM1_UP_TIM16_IRQHandler
7579 #define TIM17_IRQHandler TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM17_IRQHandler
7580 #define COMP_IRQHandler COMP2_IRQHandler
7581 #define COMP1_2_3_IRQHandler COMP2_IRQHandler
7582 #define COMP1_2_IRQHandler COMP2_IRQHandler
7583 #define COMP4_5_6_IRQHandler COMP4_6_IRQHandler
7584 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC1_IRQHandler
7585 
7586 #ifdef __cplusplus
7587 }
7588 #endif /* __cplusplus */
7589 
7590 #endif /* STM32F334x8_H */
